Kvinna till Kvinna is a Swedish foundation that provides support to women rights organisations and women human rights defenders in more than 20 countries. Kvinna till Kvinna’s Tunis office was established in 2018 and handles support to Tunisia and Egypt within our regional MENAFEM programme. In the MENA region, we currently support 50+ women’s rights organizations in the MENA region through country offices in Palestine, Lebanon and Iraq and a regional office in Amman.

- Supporting development and implementation of Kvinna till Kvinna North Africa programming;
- Maintaining a contextual understanding of organisations and trends within the women’s rights movement within North Africa and participating in relevant coordination meetings
- Making appropriate recommendations on the programme’s progress and further development as requested;
- Supporting drafting of various baseline documents, donor mapping and mapping of potential partners;
- Providing support to partner organisations through the project cycle, including i.e. identifying new partners, review of applications, reporting, monitoring and evaluation;
- Supporting capacity building efforts and organising exchanges, study trips and networking meetings to enhance quality programming and implementation;

ONSHOR is a program jointly implemented by the Financial Services Volunteer Corps
(FSVC) and the Tunisian Association of Public Controllers (ATCP), with the support of the
U.S. Middle-East Partnership Initiative (MEPI). ONSHOR aims to stimulate the dissemination
of public information. To achieve this, ONSHOR is :
• Strengthening the regulatory framework governing access to public information;
• Assist public institutions in implementing the Access to Information Act;
• Facilitate the formulation of requests for access to information by supporting &quot;applicants&quot; in the
preparation and follow-up of their requests;
• Encourage the publication of public data in an open (Open Data) format, i.e., reusable and free
of rights;
• Create value-added services from Open Data, such as Web and mobile applications.
ONSHOR addresses public institutions (ministries, public companies, local authorities, ...). This
program also collaborates with civil society in the various phases of the project.
